1.)

I chose 4 data sets from the link that you gave, which are Residential Building Data Set, Sport articles, Las Vegas Trip Advisor Reviews and Parkinsons. All includes the certain characteristics that you expect(i.e.more than 20 features, larger than 200 samples)Due to the fact that these all four do not have test data, i splitted to train and test data for each dataset as you can see as you move forward. - Residential Building data is regression problem,which aims to predict contruction project’s actual sales price,‘V-9’ variable. It has also more than 50 features. - Sport articles data set includes more than 50 features. Y is a categorical variable which is ‘obj_subj’. What the aim is to classify the data according to the y variable. - Las Vegas Trip Advisor Reviews data set has 20 attributes and also includes some categorical and ordinal variables. In this data set, Score variable is tried to be predicted. - Parkinsons data set includes 21 attributes and has some class imbalance,approximately 3:1. The purpose is to predict ‘status’, which is a categorical variable.

I will model of each data set according to Penalized Regression Approaches, Decision Trees, Support Vector Machines, Random Forests, Stochastic Gradient Boosting. Therefore, in the second part, i slitted to 4 subparts according to each dataset that i mentioned above. I will apply all algorithms you defined for each data set. In the third part, i tuned parameters for each 4 data set and each model that you gave. I know that a for loop should be created and all codes should be included in it but i could not do that. I know my error but the reason why i did not do such way is that at first i did not think such way. Then, in order to change it i did not have enough time In the fourth part, tests are done and some results are presented.

Lambda.min gives the minimum mean cross validated error. When mse is the least,log(lambda) value is important for me.Log(lambda) provide you to select lambda that minimises error. The log of the optimal value of lambda is approximately 2 in this case.Smallest number of coefficients also gives a good accuracy

  • Support Vector Machines

In this part, C values should be considered.Actually this parameter tells the SVM optimization how much you want to avoid misclassifying each training example. For example, if you are working with large values of C, the optimization will choose a smaller-margin hyperplane if that hyperplane does a better job of getting all the training points classified correctly. Conversely, a very small value of C will cause the optimizer to look for a larger-margin separating hyperplane, even if that hyperplane misclassifies more points. This parameter is used both polynomial and radial. Default value is 1. I tried 3 parameter values for C, which are 0,2,3.
